 \frac{2n + \cos(\pi n) - 5}{4} = \frac{2n + (-1)^n - 5}{4} = \left\{ \begin{array}{cc} \frac{n - 3}{2} & n \text{ is odd}\\ \frac{n - 2}{2} & n \text{ is even} \end{array} \right. 
 {\left(\frac{n+1}{2}\right)}^{\left(\frac{\cos(\pi n + \pi)+1}{2}\right)} = {\left(\frac{n+1}{2}\right)}^{\left(\frac{(-1)^{n+1}+1}{2}\right)} = \left\{ \begin{array}{cc} \frac{n + 1}{2} & n \text{ is odd}\\ 1 & n \text{ is even} \end{array} \right. 
